  "prompt": "What are the top ten PC games ever?",
  "response": "Determining the \"top ten PC games ever\" is inherently subjective, as preferences vary based on genre, gameplay mechanics, storytelling, and personal experiences. However, considering factors like critical acclaim, influence on the gaming industry, longevity, and player popularity, the following list highlights some of the most celebrated PC games up to 2023:\n\n1. **The Witcher 3: Wild Hunt**\n   - *Developer:* CD Projekt Red\n   - *Release Year:* 2015\n   - *Overview:* Renowned for its deep narrative, expansive open world, and rich character development, \"The Witcher 3\" offers an immersive fantasy experience that has set a benchmark for RPGs.\n\n2. **Half-Life 2**\n   - *Developer:* Valve Corporation\n   - *Release Year:* 2004\n   - *Overview:* A groundbreaking first-person shooter that combines innovative physics-based gameplay with a compelling story, establishing Valve as a leader in game design.\n\n3. **Minecraft**\n   - *Developer:* Mojang Studios\n   - *Release Year:* 2011\n   - *Overview:* A sandbox game that emphasizes creativity and exploration, \"Minecraft\" has become a cultural phenomenon, appealing to players of all ages and inspiring countless mods and community projects.\n\n4. **Portal 2**\n   - *Developer:* Valve Corporation\n   - *Release Year:* 2011\n   - *Overview:* This puzzle-platformer is celebrated for its clever level design, humorous writing, and innovative mechanics involving portal-based puzzles, offering both single-player and cooperative experiences.\n\n5. **World of Warcraft**\n   - *Developer:* Blizzard Entertainment\n   - *Release Year:* 2004\n   - *Overview:* As one of the most influential MMORPGs, \"World of Warcraft\" has maintained a massive player base for over a decade, featuring a rich lore, expansive content updates, and a vibrant community.\n\n6. **Doom (1993)**\n   - *Developer:* id Software\n   - *Release Year:* 1993\n   - *Overview:* A seminal first-person shooter that popularized the genre, \"Doom\" is lauded for its fast-paced action, moddability, and pioneering use of 3D graphics and networked multiplayer.\n\n7. **Sid Meier\u2019s Civilization VI**\n   - *Developer:* Firaxis Games\n   - *Release Year:* 2016\n   - *Overview:* The latest in the long-running strategy series, \"Civilization VI\" offers deep strategic gameplay where players build and expand civilizations through different historical eras.\n\n8. **StarCraft II**\n   - *Developer:* Blizzard Entertainment\n   - *Release Year:* 2010\n   - *Overview:* A highly competitive real-time strategy game known for its balanced factions, engaging storyline, and significant impact on the esports scene, particularly in South Korea.\n\n9. **Dark Souls III**\n   - *Developer:* FromSoftware\n   - *Release Year:* 2016\n   - *Overview:* Praised for its challenging gameplay, intricate world design, and deep lore, \"Dark Souls III\" has cemented its place in the action RPG genre, appealing to players seeking a tough but rewarding experience.\n\n10. **The Elder Scrolls V: Skyrim**\n    - *Developer:* Bethesda Game Studios\n    - *Release Year:* 2011\n    - *Overview:* An open-world fantasy RPG that offers unparalleled freedom, allowing players to explore a vast landscape, engage in various quests, and customize their characters extensively.\n\n**Honorable Mentions:**\n- **Grand Theft Auto V** \u2013 For its expansive open world and online multiplayer component.\n- **Counter-Strike: Global Offensive** \u2013 A staple in competitive esports.\n- **Baldur\u2019s Gate II: Shadows of Amn** \u2013 Celebrated for its rich storytelling and character development.\n- **League of Legends** \u2013 One of the most popular MOBAs with a huge global player base.\n\nEach of these games has left a significant mark on the PC gaming landscape, influencing future titles and shaping player expectations. Depending on individual tastes\u2014be it narrative-driven adventures, competitive multiplayer experiences, or creative sandbox environments\u2014different titles may resonate more strongly with different gamers.",
